SandboxStatusEventLog.name: SandboxStatusEventLog
SandboxStatusEventLog.description: SandboxStatusEventLog stores details about Sandbox copies.

CurrentSandboxOrganizationIdentifier.description: The 15-character ID of the current sandbox organization.

PendingSandboxOrganizationIdentifier.description: The 15-character ID of the target sandbox org.

RequestIdentifier.description: The unique ID of a single transaction. A transaction can contain one or more events. Each event in a given transaction has the same REQUEST_ID. For example: 3nWgxWbDKWWDIk0FKfF5DV.

SandboxOrganizationIdentifier.description: The 15-character ID of the target sandbox org.

Status.description: The status of the sandbox copy.

Timestamp.description: The access time of Salesforce services in GMT. For example: 20130715233322.670.

UserIdentifier.description: The 15-character ID of the user whoâ€™s using Salesforce services through the UI or the API. For example: 00530000009M943YAS
